				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>The focus of the analysis on the need for ‘clear and concrete actions’ which address specific constraints on producers entering particular value chains, would appear to be highly relevant. In the food and agricultural sector it suggests a need for a much greater focus on getting to grips with the specific constraints on ACP producers in profitably entering international supply chains through the elaboration of concrete and highly targeted programmes. </p><p>While there is ample evidence that this is in fact occurring in a multiplicity of sectors across the ACP, in terms of the volume of ‘aid for trade’ commitments being made, these still tend to be dominated by activities in traditional areas of engagement (e.g. infrastructure development in the road-transport sector), which may indirectly benefit disadvantaged ACP producers.</p>
		</div>
		
